HEADWORD: experienced
<hw>ex*pe"ri*enced</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧ks*p⟦emac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*⟦eit⟧nst)</pr>,
<pos>p. p. & a.</pos> <def>Taught by practice or by repeated
observations; skillful or wise by means of trials, use, or observation;
<as>as, an <ex>experienced</ex> physician, workman, soldier; an
<ex>experienced</ex> eye</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ablest and most <qex>experienced</qex> statesmen.</q>
<rj><qau>Bancroft.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Experiencer</ent>⟦br⟧
